{
  "texts": [
    "To achieve smooth interpolations, autoencoders can be combined with GANs [641], where the autoencoder acts as generator in the GAN framework, employing both an autoencoder loss and a GAN loss.",
    "B.3 Diffusion modelsDiffusion models enhanced by NNs [642][643][644] convert random noise x into a sample resembling the training data through a series of transformations.",
    "Given a data set { y 0 i } N i=1 that corresponds to the distribution q(x 0), a forward noising process q(x t |x t-1) is introduced.",
    "This process adds Gaussian noise to x t-1 at each time step t -1.",
    "The process is applied iteratively q(x 0, x 1,..., x T) = q(x 0) T t=1 q(x t |x t-1)."
  ]
}